      "content": "The argument that higher wages boost the local economy is a well-known theory, often cited by those who support increased worker compensation. In practice, for a small, rural coffee shop, the increased payroll costs will immediately strain cash flow. The benefit of higher spending power for employees is often offset by the necessity of raising prices, which can deter the very local customers you need to thrive.",
